WEBVTT

00:00.099 --> 00:03.282
<i>- Previously on</i> "Dead of Summer"...
- Let's go!

00:03.318 --> 00:06.152
All that crap written on
the walls, that's not you.

00:06.187 --> 00:07.620
You only want him 'cause
you can't have him.

00:07.656 --> 00:09.489
We have a connection.

00:09.524 --> 00:10.556
Deb? I don't get it.

00:10.592 --> 00:12.392
Staff week, she was flirty,

00:12.427 --> 00:14.293
and now it's like she flipped a switch.

00:14.329 --> 00:16.195
Ah, little light reading there, Deputy?

00:16.231 --> 00:17.330
Garrett: Found it gutted up
at the camp the other day.

00:17.365 --> 00:18.474
The heart ripped out.

00:18.475 --> 00:20.566
You think because I'm wearing this...

00:20.602 --> 00:22.535
that I'm a devil worshiper.

00:22.570 --> 00:25.605
I want you packed up
and gone by 9:00 a.m.

00:25.640 --> 00:27.440
Gonna miss you in Cabin 10, buddy.

00:27.475 --> 00:29.308
You dosed me.

00:29.344 --> 00:31.210
Oh, my God.

00:32.313 --> 00:34.247
[Water dripping]

00:37.285 --> 00:39.485
[Eerie music plays]

00:41.000 --> 00:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:00.542 --> 01:04.343
[Door opens, closes]

01:09.317 --> 01:11.551
Hello?

01:11.586 --> 01:13.486
Someone there?

01:23.231 --> 01:25.164
[Animals calling, crickets chirping]

01:34.342 --> 01:35.374
[Twig snaps]

01:46.221 --> 01:47.520
Hello?

01:47.555 --> 01:50.389
♪ ♪

02:04.274 --> 02:08.080
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

02:11.212 --> 02:14.180
Man on TV: <i>It doesn't
matter if you believe in Satan.</i>

02:14.215 --> 02:16.549
<i>It doesn't matter if
you believe in demons.</i>

02:16.584 --> 02:18.184
<i>What's important is to know</i>

02:18.219 --> 02:20.586
<i>there are people out there who do,</i>

02:20.622 --> 02:22.221
<i>and they are willing to do anything</i>

02:22.257 --> 02:23.623
<i>to accomplish their goals.</i>

02:23.658 --> 02:25.625
[TV shuts off]

02:25.660 --> 02:28.261
They say teenagers are more likely
to get wrapped up in it.

02:28.296 --> 02:30.229
I heard about this one girl.

02:30.265 --> 02:32.198
They made her drink goat's blood.

02:32.233 --> 02:33.566
Ew, Mom.

02:33.601 --> 02:35.601
Can you maybe hold the
goat's-blood talk

02:35.637 --> 02:37.270
till after breakfast?

02:37.305 --> 02:39.572
[Knock on door]

02:39.607 --> 02:41.207
Morning, Marta.

02:41.242 --> 02:43.576
DWP got mixed up again,

02:43.611 --> 02:45.178
sent your bill to our place.

02:45.213 --> 02:46.579
I mean, if they can't
get our addresses right,

02:46.614 --> 02:48.581
do we really believe the charges?

02:48.616 --> 02:50.249
I mean, come on.

02:50.285 --> 02:52.645
[Chuckles] Thank you, Erika.
Would you like some pancakes?

02:52.654 --> 02:54.287
Oh, thank you, but I couldn't.

02:54.322 --> 02:56.589
- [Footsteps approaching]
- Hector: Well, I could.

02:56.624 --> 02:58.291
Have a great day, guys.

02:58.326 --> 02:59.686
- Bye.
- Bye.

03:02.197 --> 03:03.262
Not eating, mija?

03:03.331 --> 03:05.231
I'm busting out of these jeans already.

03:05.266 --> 03:07.533
Not a really good
look if I want a prom date.

03:07.569 --> 03:11.075
Carolina, look at me.

03:12.273 --> 03:14.240
Let me tell you something.
You are beautiful.

03:14.275 --> 03:17.176
And kind.

03:17.212 --> 03:19.145
And funny. [Chuckles]

03:19.180 --> 03:21.614
So what if you don't
look like these bimbos on TV?

03:21.649 --> 03:24.283
Not everyone sees things
the way that you do, Dad.

03:24.319 --> 03:27.553
Boys, the right kind of boys,

03:27.589 --> 03:29.255
they'll notice how special you are.

03:29.290 --> 03:32.258
It happened for your mother and me.

03:32.293 --> 03:34.293
It'll happen for you, too.

03:34.329 --> 03:36.629
[Sighs]

03:36.664 --> 03:38.564
We'll see. [Chuckles]

03:38.600 --> 03:40.600
[Soft music plays]

03:43.671 --> 03:46.172
Blair: Adding a little
art to the wall, are we?

03:46.207 --> 03:47.573
Hmm. This one looks better

03:47.609 --> 03:49.308
than the one by Hard-On's bunk.

03:49.344 --> 03:51.611
Nice move, by the
way, making people think

03:51.646 --> 03:53.246
it's been up there since
we were campers.

03:53.248 --> 03:54.614
That's not desperate at all.

03:54.649 --> 03:56.282
[Sighs] What you call desperate,

03:56.317 --> 03:58.184
I call creating a myth.

03:58.219 --> 03:59.652
- [Sighs]
- Don't give me that mixtape crap.

03:59.687 --> 04:00.955
I know what I'm doing.

04:00.956 --> 04:02.503
Fine, but you don't even know Alex.

04:02.504 --> 04:05.157
I mean, you haven't seen him
since '84, so why do you want him?

04:05.193 --> 04:06.592
He's just a trophy to you.

04:06.628 --> 04:08.561
What's wrong with a trophy?

04:08.596 --> 04:10.563
[Heavy breathing]

04:10.598 --> 04:12.164
[Scoffs]

04:14.636 --> 04:17.236
♪ ♪

04:17.272 --> 04:20.172
Jessie: Big night tomorrow.
Where should we go?

04:20.208 --> 04:22.208
Alex: Not like we have many choices.

04:22.243 --> 04:25.544
We have the Plaza and... the Plaza!

04:25.580 --> 04:27.213
[Laughs]

04:27.248 --> 04:29.148
The Plaza?

04:29.183 --> 04:31.223
- Townee bar. Not your scene.
- And why is that?

04:31.252 --> 04:33.619
Something tells me you're not
a beer-and-wings type of girl.

04:33.655 --> 04:35.588
Drew: Oh, yeah, beer
and wings. Great scene.

04:35.623 --> 04:37.623
Oh, 'cause you're way too
cool for that, right?

04:37.659 --> 04:39.558
I think we all could use the break.

04:39.594 --> 04:42.628
It's only been a week, and
I've already had two bed wetters.

04:42.664 --> 04:45.231
- [Laughter]
- Cabin 10 hasn't exactly

04:45.266 --> 04:47.233
been a picnic to manage solo.

04:47.268 --> 04:48.634
Maybe if you hadn't dosed Blotter,

04:48.670 --> 04:50.269
you wouldn't have that problem.

04:50.305 --> 04:51.637
Look, I didn't dose anyone,

04:51.673 --> 04:53.239
and it was his drug dealer

04:53.274 --> 04:54.634
that led Anton out into the woods.

04:54.642 --> 04:55.965
Allegedly.

04:55.966 --> 04:57.610
You think it could've been someone else?

04:57.645 --> 04:59.245
Or nobody. For all we know,
he could've imagined him.

04:59.280 --> 05:02.181
Ah, here he comes.

05:02.216 --> 05:03.549
[Sighs] Spielberg with the schedule.

05:03.584 --> 05:05.184
Spielberg. Well, I love some

05:05.219 --> 05:07.153
"Raiders of the Lost Ark" action,

05:07.188 --> 05:09.188
but I'm more of an indie
guy... Jarmusch, Lee, Scorsese...

05:09.223 --> 05:10.589
Joel, schedule?

05:10.625 --> 05:12.258
Who's got the night
off and who's stuck here...

05:12.293 --> 05:14.193
Working the most awesome movie
night we've ever had?

05:14.228 --> 05:16.562
Seriously, Joel, who's helping
you with said movie night?

05:16.597 --> 05:18.597
Blair, Jessie, and...

05:18.633 --> 05:20.166
Drew.

05:20.201 --> 05:22.168
[Laughs]

05:22.203 --> 05:24.603
- Can't wait.
- Bring that enthusiasm.

05:27.642 --> 05:29.575
Blair: So, movie night will be fun.

05:29.610 --> 05:32.578
Cricket: So, Alex,

05:32.613 --> 05:34.580
you should stop by the art studio later,

05:34.615 --> 05:36.182
if you're free.

05:36.217 --> 05:39.185
Yeah, we'll see how my day goes.

05:40.254 --> 05:42.521
♪ ♪

05:52.433 --> 05:54.266
[Door opens]

06:03.578 --> 06:05.478
Cricket?

06:07.348 --> 06:09.215
Cricket.

06:09.250 --> 06:11.317
You've got to be kidding me.

06:11.352 --> 06:13.219
[Scoffs] Don't be so dramatic.

06:13.254 --> 06:15.154
Last time I checked, you were a virgin.

06:15.189 --> 06:17.149
[Sighs] It's just a little experiment.

06:17.158 --> 06:18.491
[School bell rings]

06:18.526 --> 06:20.426
Cricket, you don't want sex.

06:20.461 --> 06:21.560
You want... a mixtape,

06:21.596 --> 06:24.430
someone that's into
you because they know you.

06:24.465 --> 06:27.466
Nope, just the sex, thanks.

06:27.502 --> 06:31.203
You're better than this.

06:35.643 --> 06:38.511
Wow. That's creative. Cool.

06:40.581 --> 06:43.115
Oh, that's awesome. Good work.

06:44.552 --> 06:46.452
[Chuckles] Very funny.

06:46.487 --> 06:49.288
I didn't write that.

06:49.323 --> 06:51.257
[Eerie music plays]

06:55.196 --> 06:56.595
Robotic voice: <i>Aardvark.</i>

06:56.631 --> 06:59.165
<i>Aardvark. Armadillo.</i>

06:59.200 --> 07:00.533
<i>Armadillo.</i>

07:00.568 --> 07:03.302
Mm. It's camp. Try enjoying nature.

07:04.539 --> 07:07.373
Hmm. Looks like I've
got a date to plan for.

07:07.408 --> 07:09.308
Yeah, but how would Alex know that...

07:09.343 --> 07:12.578
He's smart, and if it wasn't you,
who else would it be?

07:15.444 --> 07:17.610
French fry for your thoughts?

07:17.612 --> 07:20.586
[Sighs] I'm still thinking
about that kid up by camp,

07:20.621 --> 07:24.205
you know, what he said,

07:24.206 --> 07:25.827
that someone was going to die.

07:25.828 --> 07:29.295
This deer, Dave, now this kid...

07:29.330 --> 07:31.944
Something's happening by that lake.

07:31.945 --> 07:33.285
And one of the
counselors told me they found

07:33.286 --> 07:34.500
an old cabin out
there, some real creepy stuff.

07:34.535 --> 07:37.323
I was gonna go check it out later

07:37.450 --> 07:39.343
if you could spare me from
speeding-ticket duty for awhile.

07:39.465 --> 07:40.630
Does it matter what I say?

07:40.751 --> 07:42.499
I thought I'd give you the
courtesy of asking first.

07:42.640 --> 07:43.861
Yeah, thanks for that.

07:45.379 --> 07:48.614
So you really believe this
is all tied together, Garrett?

07:48.649 --> 07:50.449
I don't know.

07:51.652 --> 07:55.091
But I do believe that something
is going on at that camp.

08:04.332 --> 08:06.665
♪ ♪

08:09.537 --> 08:11.565
Hello?

08:11.698 --> 08:13.712
[Distant growling]

08:25.720 --> 08:27.653
[Suspenseful music plays]

08:33.427 --> 08:34.760
[Gasps]

08:34.794 --> 08:37.763
[Breathing heavily]

08:37.798 --> 08:39.331
[Twig snaps]

08:42.537 --> 08:46.035
[Screaming]

08:51.345 --> 08:53.412
Ugh!

08:53.447 --> 08:54.780
[Screams]

08:54.815 --> 08:59.566
[Gasps, breathing heavily]

09:04.339 --> 09:06.239
Ouch!

09:06.275 --> 09:08.341
- Ah!
- Not a tetherball girl?

09:08.377 --> 09:11.244
Uh, I was better at the horseshoes.

09:11.280 --> 09:13.546
Hey, Cricket, do you want
to come and take my place?

09:13.582 --> 09:15.181
Cricket?

09:17.586 --> 09:19.486
Are you okay?

09:19.521 --> 09:20.934
[Soft music plays]

09:20.935 --> 09:22.470
Yeah. I'm fine.

09:22.491 --> 09:25.425
Well, I had a bad dream last night.

09:25.460 --> 09:27.260
What happened?

09:27.296 --> 09:31.264
There were these people wearing masks,

09:31.300 --> 09:34.167
and there was a bonfire.

09:34.202 --> 09:35.602
[Suspenseful music plays]

09:35.637 --> 09:38.571
[Screaming]

09:38.607 --> 09:42.342
I think they were
doing some kind of ritual.

09:42.377 --> 09:44.149
My boots were sinking into the ground

09:44.150 --> 09:45.469
like it was quicksand.

09:45.733 --> 09:48.248
- I know it sounds ridiculous but...
- No.

09:48.283 --> 09:51.551
A-After all that happened
with Dave and then Anton,

09:51.586 --> 09:53.186
I think we're all a little jumpy.

09:53.221 --> 09:54.541
Well, I've had nightmares before.

09:54.556 --> 09:55.622
This was different.

09:55.657 --> 09:57.617
When I woke up, I
couldn't find my boots.

09:57.626 --> 10:00.327
Jessie: Your boots? During
week one of camp?

10:00.362 --> 10:02.202
Maybe you didn't even bring them.

10:02.464 --> 10:04.297
Look...

10:04.333 --> 10:09.235
my first night here, I
thought I was seeing things, too.

10:09.271 --> 10:11.638
But the truth was it was in my head

10:11.673 --> 10:15.408
because I was upset
about something else.

10:15.444 --> 10:19.346
And once I realized
that, I stopped seeing them.

10:19.381 --> 10:21.414
You will, too. Don't worry.

10:33.562 --> 10:34.627
Hi, Garrett.

10:34.663 --> 10:36.429
Garrett?

10:36.465 --> 10:38.498
I mean Deputy. I mean [chuckles] hi.

10:38.533 --> 10:39.804
Garrett's fine.

10:39.955 --> 10:42.369
Uh, so, what brings you out here?

10:42.404 --> 10:43.675
Tying up some loose ends.

10:43.829 --> 10:46.206
Saw some campers unrolling
the big screen on the lawn.

10:46.241 --> 10:47.240
Yeah, it's movie night.

10:47.275 --> 10:48.555
Remember those well.

10:48.577 --> 10:49.642
Hope it's something good.

10:49.678 --> 10:52.512
I actually have the night
off, headed into town...

10:52.547 --> 10:54.547
some place called the
Plaza. You know it?

10:54.549 --> 10:57.069
Know it? My mother's worked
there for years.

10:57.329 --> 10:59.352
Will you be out tonight, too?

10:59.388 --> 11:01.321
I'm on popcorn duty.

11:01.356 --> 11:03.156
That's too bad.

11:03.191 --> 11:04.557
[Soft music plays]

11:07.229 --> 11:09.462
[Rustling]

11:15.437 --> 11:18.171
[Ominous music plays]

11:30.652 --> 11:32.385
Hey!

11:32.421 --> 11:34.254
[Laughter]

11:34.289 --> 11:35.321
[Gasps]

11:35.357 --> 11:37.257
Little jumpy, are we?

11:37.292 --> 11:38.802
Did you see that?

11:38.935 --> 11:40.496
Those little pervs were spying on me.

11:40.499 --> 11:42.562
I could see why. You're hot.

11:42.597 --> 11:44.230
Yeah, to the prepubescent set.

11:44.266 --> 11:45.183
Blotter thought so.

11:45.185 --> 11:47.600
Hey, one, I was never into
him, and, two, he's gone.

11:47.636 --> 11:50.121
His bunkmate, on the other hand...

11:50.122 --> 11:52.439
You really think Alex is
going to be waiting by the lake?

11:52.474 --> 11:55.275
It's almost noon. Time to find out.

11:59.381 --> 12:02.482
[Bomb the Bass' "Beat Dis" plays]

12:02.517 --> 12:05.518
[All chanting "Chug, chug,
chug, chug, chug, chug"]

12:05.554 --> 12:08.354
[Cheering]

12:19.267 --> 12:20.633
[Sighs]

12:20.669 --> 12:21.634
Worst party ever.

12:21.670 --> 12:23.570
But at least there's refreshments.

12:23.605 --> 12:24.504
Do you want one?

12:24.539 --> 12:26.406
Six months till summer.

12:26.441 --> 12:28.441
I'm wearing a bikini at camp this year.

12:28.477 --> 12:31.244
Ah. So, you're going to be a thin slut.

12:31.279 --> 12:32.345
Excellent.

12:32.380 --> 12:34.314
- [Chuckles]
- I'm going to be noticed.

12:34.349 --> 12:37.183
Not one guy has come up
and talked to me tonight.

12:37.219 --> 12:38.618
Who cares? In six months,

12:38.653 --> 12:40.587
we're never going to see
any of these losers again,

12:40.622 --> 12:43.423
so I say we get out of
here and go see a movie.

12:43.458 --> 12:45.525
"Scrooged" again?

12:45.560 --> 12:47.494
Yeah.

12:47.529 --> 12:50.196
Sure. Whatever.

12:50.232 --> 12:51.331
All right. Let's go.

12:51.366 --> 12:54.234
♪ ♪

12:56.304 --> 12:58.671
- Cricket, right?
- Yeah.

12:58.707 --> 12:59.719
I'm Travis.

12:59.827 --> 13:01.541
Nice to meet you, Travis.
We were actually leaving.

13:01.576 --> 13:02.542
Come on, Cricket.

13:04.513 --> 13:07.313
This is my house. I
could give you the tour.

13:07.349 --> 13:09.249
It's a garage.

13:09.284 --> 13:10.564
There's an inside.

13:11.353 --> 13:12.633
Would you like to see it?

13:15.223 --> 13:16.589
Lead the way.

13:27.302 --> 13:29.302
[Bird cawing]

13:37.245 --> 13:40.346
♪ ♪

14:05.640 --> 14:07.574
[Notes play off-key]

14:31.266 --> 14:33.299
[Rustling]

15:10.102 --> 15:12.936
Heading in for a dip?

15:12.972 --> 15:15.973
You're that drug dealer, right?

15:16.008 --> 15:17.968
Well, my friends usually call me Damon.

15:17.977 --> 15:19.257
We're not friends.

15:19.278 --> 15:21.144
Ooh. That's not very nice, is it?

15:21.180 --> 15:23.246
Well, you don't seem
like a very nice boy.

15:23.282 --> 15:26.149
You're not exactly giving
me a chance, are you?

15:26.185 --> 15:28.118
Get out of here, Damon.

15:28.153 --> 15:30.921
Last I checked, this
lake was open to the public.

15:32.024 --> 15:34.958
All right. All right. We're going.

15:34.994 --> 15:37.826
And you think I'm the
one who isn't very nice.

15:47.172 --> 15:50.107
You okay? He try to hurt you?

15:50.142 --> 15:51.942
I'm fine.

15:51.977 --> 15:53.977
[INXS' "Never Tear Us Apart" plays]

15:57.016 --> 15:59.850
♪ Don't ask me ♪

15:59.885 --> 16:03.120
♪ What you know is true ♪

16:03.155 --> 16:05.155
♪ Don't have to tell you ♪

16:07.126 --> 16:10.961
♪ I love your precious heart ♪

16:10.996 --> 16:15.999
♪ I, I was standing ♪

16:16.035 --> 16:17.034
[Laughs]

16:17.069 --> 16:19.036
♪ Two worlds collided ♪

16:19.071 --> 16:20.871
[Bell rings]

16:20.906 --> 16:24.274
♪ And they could never tear us apart ♪

16:27.179 --> 16:29.212
[Sobbing]

16:34.053 --> 16:35.919
You were right. It wasn't Alex.

16:35.954 --> 16:36.953
So what?

16:36.989 --> 16:38.288
You're just gonna stay in and mope?

16:38.323 --> 16:39.890
It's your night off.

16:39.925 --> 16:42.259
Go put on a dress, show
off that hot bod,

16:42.294 --> 16:45.128
and if Alex doesn't notice
you, someone else will.

16:45.164 --> 16:47.124
Can't I just go to movie night with you?

16:47.132 --> 16:50.100
Um, I have my own agenda, and
comforting you is not on it.

16:50.135 --> 16:53.336
So, get your skinny ass dressed.
This night is not over yet.

16:53.372 --> 16:56.339
Damn right. It's just getting started.

16:56.375 --> 16:57.375
[Scoffs] Can we help you?

16:57.376 --> 17:00.177
You can't. But you can.

17:01.246 --> 17:02.849
Maybe something family friendly

17:02.850 --> 17:05.082
that the kids will
love, like "E.T." or "Dumbo".

17:05.117 --> 17:06.148
No. Let's go edgier.

17:06.185 --> 17:08.085
Edgier at camp? [Laughs]

17:08.119 --> 17:11.054
Well, I'm not talking David
Lynch "Blue Velvet" edgy,

17:11.089 --> 17:13.290
but maybe gateway edgy.

17:13.325 --> 17:14.925
Okay.

17:14.960 --> 17:18.194
"Five Easy Pieces," "Harold and Maude."

17:18.230 --> 17:21.998
I'm not really sure
that our kids are ready

17:22.034 --> 17:24.166
for a film about an older
woman and a younger man.

17:24.203 --> 17:26.936
Come on. It's about so
much more than that.

17:26.972 --> 17:28.070
No, I get that.

17:28.107 --> 17:30.006
I love Hal Ashby. Have
you seen "Shampoo"?

17:30.042 --> 17:31.975
- Of course.
- [Laughs]

17:32.010 --> 17:35.245
You really were born about 20
years too late, weren't you?

17:35.280 --> 17:36.913
The best things in life are timeless.

17:36.949 --> 17:39.282
Mm.

17:39.318 --> 17:41.118
Hey.

17:41.153 --> 17:42.219
Yeah?

17:45.124 --> 17:47.124
You know, most people, they
don't understand me.

17:48.961 --> 17:50.961
But I feel like I
could talk to you all night.

17:52.064 --> 17:54.264
- Deb?
- Yes, sweetheart?

17:54.299 --> 17:56.266
It's Jessie. Her grandma died.

17:56.301 --> 17:58.268
Oh.

18:03.008 --> 18:04.141
[Creaking]

18:04.176 --> 18:06.977
[Sighs] Yank it somewhere else, dweebs!

18:09.014 --> 18:11.815
[Rustling]

18:16.188 --> 18:18.188
♪ ♪

18:26.965 --> 18:28.326
[Screams]

18:34.339 --> 18:39.042
Robotic voice: <i>Don't. Don't. Don't.</i>

18:39.077 --> 18:40.143
<i>Don't.</i>

18:40.179 --> 18:42.145
<i>Don't.</i>

18:42.181 --> 18:45.882
<i>Don't.</i>

18:45.918 --> 18:47.851
<i>Don't.</i>

18:47.886 --> 18:49.986
<i>Don't.</i>

18:50.022 --> 18:51.888
<i>Don't.</i>

18:51.924 --> 18:54.891
<i>Go.</i>

18:54.927 --> 18:57.260
<i>Don't go.</i>

18:57.296 --> 18:59.357
<i>Don't go.</i>

19:07.463 --> 19:09.196
Hey.

19:11.701 --> 19:13.300
Deb: Jessie.

19:13.336 --> 19:15.536
I'm so sorry about your grandmother.

19:15.571 --> 19:16.637
Thank you.

19:16.672 --> 19:19.506
Please let me know if there's
anything I can do.

19:19.542 --> 19:22.509
[Sighs] Amy, I have a
humongous favor to ask.

19:22.545 --> 19:23.237
Yes, sure.

19:23.262 --> 19:25.312
Could you please take
Jessie's shift tonight?

19:25.348 --> 19:28.248
I think she could really
use a night off work.

19:28.284 --> 19:29.350
Of course.

19:29.385 --> 19:32.219
Thank you. Okay, everyone, have fun.

19:32.254 --> 19:33.621
Be safe.

19:34.690 --> 19:37.625
Okay. Let's go, guys.

19:37.660 --> 19:39.627
The Plaza calls. Come on, Cricket.

19:39.662 --> 19:43.397
There's a screwdriver
waiting with your name on it.

19:43.432 --> 19:45.432
Well played.

19:45.468 --> 19:48.235
I can't believe you made
me lie about your grandma.

19:48.270 --> 19:50.638
She did die... eight years ago.

19:50.673 --> 19:52.673
[Chuckles]

19:52.708 --> 19:54.708
Garrett: Yeah, hi. This is Deputy Sykes.

19:54.744 --> 19:57.478
I need to get into the archives.

19:57.513 --> 20:01.415
Does the library have any
pieces on this town's history?

20:01.450 --> 20:04.418
I'm looking for stuff from
the 1860s, 1870s, maybe.

20:04.453 --> 20:07.254
Anything unusual that happened
at the lake around that time.

20:07.289 --> 20:08.689
Great.

20:08.724 --> 20:10.624
I can be down first
thing in the morning.

20:10.660 --> 20:11.692
Thank you.

20:11.727 --> 20:12.693
♪ And oh ♪

20:12.728 --> 20:14.728
Buy me a drink, townee?

20:14.764 --> 20:19.433
♪ I can't do without you for too long ♪

20:19.468 --> 20:21.468
♪ You're my situation ♪

20:23.104 --> 20:25.339
So, where is it?

20:25.374 --> 20:27.454
The screwdriver with my name on it.

20:27.476 --> 20:29.677
[Scoffs] How'd you know I like those?

20:29.712 --> 20:32.713
Well, you drank O.J. as if it
was water when we were campers.

20:32.748 --> 20:34.715
Hey, remember when you puked orange

20:34.750 --> 20:36.470
in the middle of color wars?

20:36.485 --> 20:37.551
- ♪ My kinda lover ♪
- [Chuckles]

20:37.586 --> 20:38.652
Yo!

20:38.688 --> 20:41.455
Uh, excuse me.

20:41.490 --> 20:43.390
I got to, you know...

20:43.426 --> 20:45.459
♪ You keep me all together ♪

20:45.494 --> 20:50.397
♪ You take me out whenever
I'm lettin' down ♪

20:52.768 --> 20:54.768
♪ You got the motions, baby ♪

20:54.804 --> 20:57.671
Your boyfriend leave you all alone?

20:57.707 --> 21:00.507
He's not my boyfriend.

21:00.543 --> 21:01.542
Mm. His loss.

21:01.577 --> 21:04.244
♪ And oh ♪

21:04.280 --> 21:05.345
Want a brewski?

21:05.381 --> 21:07.281
Sorry, I don't hang with people

21:07.316 --> 21:09.283
who use the term "brewski."

21:09.318 --> 21:11.318
♪ I can't see no reason ♪

21:11.353 --> 21:14.254
Just one sec.

21:14.290 --> 21:16.490
♪ My kinda lover ♪

21:16.525 --> 21:17.591
What are you doing?

21:17.626 --> 21:18.625
He's a townee.

21:18.661 --> 21:20.541
I didn't come here to meet townees.

21:20.563 --> 21:22.396
Hey, don't knock townees, okay?

21:22.431 --> 21:24.298
They're not all bad.

21:24.333 --> 21:26.300
Okay, "A," he's not exactly hideous.

21:26.335 --> 21:27.335
♪ My kinda lover ♪

21:27.336 --> 21:29.056
He wants you. You want Alex.

21:30.506 --> 21:33.640
Use him to make Alex jealous.

21:33.676 --> 21:36.577
So evil.

21:36.612 --> 21:39.346
[Chuckles] I love it.

21:39.381 --> 21:40.414
Thank you.

21:40.449 --> 21:41.515
♪ Rock me, sock me ♪

21:41.550 --> 21:44.752
♪ Baby, you got me ridin' to the end ♪

21:44.787 --> 21:46.320
♪ Rake me, shake me ♪

21:46.355 --> 21:48.722
♪ Baby, you make me turn me on again ♪

21:48.758 --> 21:51.725
[Sighs] Yeah. How 'bout that brewski?

21:51.761 --> 21:53.660
♪ You got my motor racin' ♪

21:53.696 --> 21:55.562
What do you say, Deputy?

21:55.598 --> 21:58.465
A little Foosball for old time's sake?

22:01.504 --> 22:04.304
♪ I wanna set you reelin' ♪

22:04.340 --> 22:05.672
♪ I wanna make you
feel the way that I do ♪

22:05.708 --> 22:08.675
So... you want to get some fresh air?

22:08.711 --> 22:10.644
I could use a smoke.

22:10.679 --> 22:14.481
We could go for a ride.
My Firebird's out back.

22:14.517 --> 22:17.451
My mom warned me about people like you.

22:17.486 --> 22:20.354
Didn't your mom also tell you
not to judge a book by its cover?

22:20.389 --> 22:22.389
♪ You're my kinda lover ♪

22:22.424 --> 22:24.291
♪ My kinda lover ♪

22:24.326 --> 22:25.646
You know, you have beautiful hair.

22:25.661 --> 22:28.262
♪ My kinda lover ♪

22:28.297 --> 22:29.657
You ever think of letting it down?

22:29.665 --> 22:32.499
♪ My kinda lover ♪

22:32.535 --> 22:34.501
♪ My kinda lover ♪

22:34.537 --> 22:38.338
♪ My kinda lover ♪

22:39.475 --> 22:41.408
May I?

22:41.443 --> 22:43.710
♪ My kinda lover ♪

22:43.746 --> 22:45.312
♪ My kinda lover ♪

22:45.347 --> 22:47.581
Suits you.

22:47.616 --> 22:48.882
♪ My kinda lover ♪

22:48.918 --> 22:51.451
So, you gonna spend all night
trying to make that idiot jealous,

22:51.487 --> 22:52.586
or are you gonna let me take
you for a ride around the block?

22:52.621 --> 22:54.521
♪ My kinda lover ♪

22:54.557 --> 22:55.756
One ride.

22:57.493 --> 23:00.350
♪ My kinda lover ♪

23:03.974 --> 23:05.574
This is a travesty.

23:05.609 --> 23:07.843
Nobody takes care of film anymore.

23:07.878 --> 23:09.845
Look at these marks.

23:09.880 --> 23:12.681
"Time Bandits" is an American classic.

23:12.716 --> 23:13.849
It deserves respect.

23:13.884 --> 23:15.717
I loved that film.

23:15.753 --> 23:19.555
Robin Hood, Napoleon... all
that time travel was really cool.

23:19.590 --> 23:21.990
Oh, damn it. Would you
hand me that splicer?

23:22.026 --> 23:23.892
Yeah.

23:26.597 --> 23:28.931
You know, some people say

23:28.966 --> 23:31.800
all that stuff was in that kid's head.

23:31.836 --> 23:33.702
I don't believe that.

23:33.737 --> 23:35.771
Isn't reality all in our heads, too?

23:35.806 --> 23:38.193
Yeah. That's a good point.

23:39.677 --> 23:40.976
We're all set.

23:41.011 --> 23:42.945
Awesome. I can't wait to watch it again.

23:42.980 --> 23:44.947
Aren't you upset?

23:44.982 --> 23:45.981
About what?

23:46.016 --> 23:47.916
That you're stuck here tonight,

23:47.952 --> 23:49.718
away from Sykes.

23:49.753 --> 23:50.819
He'll be fine.

23:50.855 --> 23:52.788
I'm sure Jessie's all
over him right now, anyway.

23:52.823 --> 23:54.623
Her grandma just died.

23:54.658 --> 23:55.724
Her grandma didn't die.

23:55.759 --> 23:58.527
She just didn't want me around,

23:58.562 --> 24:00.863
getting between her and Garrett.

24:00.898 --> 24:02.898
Why didn't you say anything?

24:02.933 --> 24:07.803
Because camp is about
more than finding a guy for me.

24:07.838 --> 24:11.740
It's about having
friends, making friends,

24:11.775 --> 24:13.695
and the last way to do
that is by making an enemy

24:13.711 --> 24:15.577
out of someone like Jessie.

24:15.613 --> 24:18.614
You are super Zen.

24:18.649 --> 24:20.015
[Chuckles]

24:20.050 --> 24:22.885
[Heavy metal music plays]

24:36.634 --> 24:39.568
[Sighs] Thanks for walking me home.

24:39.603 --> 24:41.937
I just couldn't deal with school today.

24:43.073 --> 24:45.874
Six more months, Cricket.

24:45.910 --> 24:47.910
Six more months.

24:58.989 --> 25:00.856
[Clattering]

25:03.961 --> 25:05.894
♪ ♪

25:12.603 --> 25:15.003
[Indistinct whispering]

25:21.845 --> 25:22.878
Carolina.

25:22.913 --> 25:24.913
I can explain.

25:24.949 --> 25:27.783
Don't... Don't tell
your mother. She'd die.

25:27.818 --> 25:29.818
Carolina!

25:37.962 --> 25:40.829
[Engine revs, tires screech]

25:43.033 --> 25:45.767
Kind of fast, no?

25:46.837 --> 25:48.837
[Tires screech]

25:48.872 --> 25:50.639
Geez, slow down!

25:50.674 --> 25:52.574
[Engine revs]

25:56.046 --> 25:58.513
[Dramatic music plays]

26:01.986 --> 26:03.885
You.

26:03.921 --> 26:05.787
It was you.

26:07.725 --> 26:09.591
[Laughs]

26:09.627 --> 26:11.593
Let me out. Aah!

26:12.696 --> 26:13.695
[Tires squeal]

26:15.633 --> 26:17.633
- Oh!
- [Siren wailing]

26:17.668 --> 26:18.934
Aah!

26:24.041 --> 26:25.907
What the hell are you doing here?

26:25.943 --> 26:27.909
Her friends were worried about
her getting in the car with you.

26:27.945 --> 26:30.679
- I can't imagine why.
- He's been stalking me!

26:30.714 --> 26:32.614
Stalking? Come on. She
was begging for it.

26:32.650 --> 26:33.715
What did you just say?

26:33.751 --> 26:35.617
Every camp has a whore.

26:46.930 --> 26:48.930
All right. Okay. Come
on. Come on. Enough.

26:48.932 --> 26:50.866
Let's go. Come on. That's enough.

26:50.901 --> 26:52.834
[Coughing]

26:52.870 --> 26:56.772
♪ ♪

26:56.807 --> 27:00.509
Blair: So, I thought, "Movie
night. Sure. Why not?

27:00.544 --> 27:02.878
I like movies and I like nights and..."

27:02.913 --> 27:05.814
Do you, I-I mean, like
either of those things?

27:05.849 --> 27:08.750
Well, I love movies, but
I haven't seen this one.

27:08.786 --> 27:10.719
Have you seen "Time Bandits?"

27:10.754 --> 27:13.722
Because Joel's been going
on and on about it, and I...

27:13.757 --> 27:15.190
What?

27:16.694 --> 27:18.994
♪ ♪

27:20.597 --> 27:24.566
[Molly Duncan's "Make A Journey" plays]

27:24.601 --> 27:28.770
♪ Build a pyramid to hide you ♪

27:28.806 --> 27:31.807
♪ Take an army to defend you ♪

27:31.842 --> 27:32.874
[Sighs]

27:32.910 --> 27:36.712
♪ But be sure that I will find you ♪

27:36.780 --> 27:40.916
♪ There's a season to go hunting ♪

27:40.951 --> 27:42.851
♪ There's a reason to be running ♪

27:42.886 --> 27:44.853
So...

27:44.888 --> 27:46.788
♪ Keep on searching the horizon ♪

27:46.824 --> 27:48.890
I didn't think this is
how the night would end.

27:48.926 --> 27:52.728
It hasn't ended yet.

27:52.763 --> 27:56.965
♪ Cross the desert sand ♪

27:57.000 --> 28:00.969
♪ To a far-off land ♪

28:01.004 --> 28:04.906
♪ You don't have much time ♪

28:04.942 --> 28:08.810
♪ Better say goodbye ♪

28:08.846 --> 28:11.580
♪ While you can ♪

28:11.615 --> 28:12.614
Oh! Oh!

28:12.649 --> 28:14.649
Oh! Ow! [Laughs]

28:14.685 --> 28:16.618
Ugh. Are you okay?

28:16.653 --> 28:18.587
- Yeah. Are you?
- Yeah.

28:18.622 --> 28:20.889
[Sighs]

28:21.925 --> 28:25.794
♪ Feel the cutting edge of danger ♪

28:25.829 --> 28:29.798
♪ See it glitter, I will show you ♪

28:29.833 --> 28:33.702
♪ Cross the desert sand ♪

28:33.737 --> 28:38.540
♪ To a far-off land ♪

28:38.575 --> 28:41.977
♪ You don't have much time ♪

28:42.012 --> 28:45.781
♪ Better say goodbye ♪

28:46.850 --> 28:48.750
Oh. [Chuckles]

28:48.786 --> 28:49.785
Oh.

28:54.758 --> 28:56.625
You made this?

28:56.660 --> 28:57.926
[Chuckles]

28:57.961 --> 28:59.494
No.

28:59.530 --> 29:01.963
That's from Blotter's
bunk. He left his crap here.

29:01.999 --> 29:04.933
Do you really think I
drink out of a baby bottle?

29:04.968 --> 29:07.669
Come here.

29:13.777 --> 29:16.545
Mm. Mm.

29:16.580 --> 29:18.947
I stopped by The Sharper
Image at the mall the other day,

29:18.982 --> 29:20.615
and I found something.

29:20.651 --> 29:22.551
It's perfect for your father.

29:22.586 --> 29:24.986
Have you seen those
little rotating tie racks?

29:25.022 --> 29:27.789
They... Cricket?

29:27.825 --> 29:30.625
- Sweetie, what is it?
- Mom...

29:32.696 --> 29:34.529
there's something I have to tell you.

29:34.565 --> 29:36.932
It's okay.

29:36.967 --> 29:39.968
Talk to me.

29:40.003 --> 29:41.870
Dad, he's...

29:41.905 --> 29:43.004
[Sighs]

29:43.040 --> 29:44.840
I saw him with Erika.

29:48.712 --> 29:50.779
I'm sorry you saw that, honey.

29:50.814 --> 29:53.615
Wait, what? You knew?

29:53.650 --> 29:54.683
I know. Honey, I know.

29:54.718 --> 29:56.551
Well, why don't you do something?

29:56.587 --> 29:57.986
Like what? Get a divorce?

29:58.021 --> 29:59.588
Start dating again at my age?

29:59.623 --> 30:01.857
But, Mom, you deserve better.

30:01.892 --> 30:03.892
You don't know what goes
into a marriage, Carolina.

30:03.927 --> 30:04.960
So, what?

30:04.995 --> 30:06.962
You just look the other way?

30:06.997 --> 30:10.665
Don't you have any self-respect?

30:10.701 --> 30:12.634
One of these days, you'll realize,

30:12.669 --> 30:16.004
women like us, sometimes
we have to settle.

30:20.077 --> 30:23.044
♪ ♪

30:26.850 --> 30:27.916
[Gasps]

30:27.951 --> 30:30.752
- I got to go.
- What?

30:30.787 --> 30:31.787
I got to leave. I'm sorry.

30:31.822 --> 30:32.821
Hey, hey, wait, wait. Wait.

30:32.856 --> 30:36.625
Hey, what did I do? Cricket!

30:36.660 --> 30:39.027
[Sighs]

30:39.062 --> 30:40.962
I feel terrible.

30:40.998 --> 30:42.931
I never should have let
Cricket get in the car with him.

30:42.966 --> 30:44.966
You didn't know.

30:45.002 --> 30:46.968
I thought we were walking to your cabin.

30:47.004 --> 30:48.970
We are. In a minute.

30:49.006 --> 30:51.706
[Laughter in distance]

30:51.742 --> 30:53.775
Ah, movie night.

30:53.810 --> 30:56.611
Are they still putting too
much salt on the popcorn?

30:56.647 --> 30:59.014
[Chuckles] Stillwater tradition.

30:59.049 --> 31:00.982
Some things never change.

31:01.018 --> 31:03.018
No, they don't.

31:03.053 --> 31:05.854
Here it is.

31:05.889 --> 31:07.756
I found it the other day.

31:07.791 --> 31:08.957
I completely forgotten about it.

31:08.992 --> 31:10.825
Do you remember when we carved that?

31:10.861 --> 31:12.827
Yeah, I do.

31:17.634 --> 31:20.035
Do you remember what
happened after we carved it?

31:20.070 --> 31:23.872
You know, that wasn't
just our first kiss.

31:23.907 --> 31:25.941
That was <i>my</i> first kiss.

31:25.976 --> 31:27.842
Ever.

31:27.878 --> 31:29.778
Mine too.

31:29.813 --> 31:32.647
♪ ♪

31:38.021 --> 31:39.955
I should head back.

31:56.673 --> 31:58.573
Well?

31:58.609 --> 32:01.543
Best... night... ever.

32:01.578 --> 32:03.418
- [Chuckles]
- [Chuckles] And you?

32:04.948 --> 32:06.982
[Chuckles]

32:07.017 --> 32:09.017
You got a mixtape, literally.

32:09.052 --> 32:11.753
I was so wrong about Alex.

32:11.788 --> 32:12.821
No.

32:12.856 --> 32:14.723
You were right about Blotter.

32:14.758 --> 32:17.792
And you were right about me.

32:17.828 --> 32:20.729
Turns out I do want a mixtape.

32:20.764 --> 32:22.998
And now he's gone.

32:23.033 --> 32:25.000
Well, there's always next summer.

32:25.035 --> 32:27.869
[Chuckles] Come on. Let's go.

32:32.909 --> 32:34.743
[Both laughing]

32:34.778 --> 32:36.778
♪ ♪

33:11.556 --> 33:13.455
[Door closes]

33:13.491 --> 33:16.425
Hey, Jessie.

33:16.460 --> 33:18.460
- What's that?
- Cookies for you.

33:18.496 --> 33:21.330
You know, I know exactly how you feel.

33:21.365 --> 33:23.299
My grandma died when I was 8.

33:23.334 --> 33:25.134
It was the worst.

33:26.370 --> 33:29.104
We made them for movie
night. They're still fresh.

33:29.140 --> 33:31.140
I knew you were
out, so I saved you some.

33:33.211 --> 33:35.444
When my grandma
passed, after the funeral,

33:35.479 --> 33:37.112
my best friend brought me cookies

33:37.148 --> 33:38.547
and tried to make me feel better.

33:38.583 --> 33:43.352
And the crazy thing
is, they kind of helped.

33:43.387 --> 33:45.387
So I hope they help you,

33:45.423 --> 33:48.190
even just a tiny bit.

33:49.293 --> 33:51.193
Thank you.

33:51.229 --> 33:53.128
Okay.

33:56.267 --> 33:59.068
[Chuckles]

33:59.103 --> 34:01.170
Heelan: I don't like
it any more than you do,

34:01.205 --> 34:02.811
but it's he said/she said.

34:02.956 --> 34:05.407
Having a red marker in
your glove box ain't a crime.

34:05.443 --> 34:07.443
Neither's owning a knife.

34:07.478 --> 34:09.445
- We had to let Crowley go.
- Read this.

34:09.480 --> 34:12.281
- What is it?
- Read it.

34:12.315 --> 34:14.283
It's from a soldier from 1871.

34:14.318 --> 34:16.150
It's his journal.

34:16.187 --> 34:17.186
Checked that out of the library.

34:17.221 --> 34:18.254
They've got collections going back

34:18.289 --> 34:20.289
farther than you'd think.

34:20.324 --> 34:23.092
Uh... "The spiritualist cult

34:23.127 --> 34:27.463
led by the imperious
leader known only as Holyoke

34:27.498 --> 34:29.431
met a horrific end at
our hands last night.

34:29.467 --> 34:32.434
Holyoke's followers
believed Lake Stillwater

34:32.469 --> 34:34.370
held supernatural power

34:34.405 --> 34:36.338
and were trying to summon said power

34:36.373 --> 34:37.373
through an occult ritual

34:37.408 --> 34:39.408
before their deaths brought an end

34:39.443 --> 34:42.344
to their unholy pursuits."

34:42.380 --> 34:44.255
Unholy pursuits?

34:44.382 --> 34:47.181
Apparently, when they found
him, he was playing the piano.

34:47.217 --> 34:49.150
The villagers dragged
him out, killed him,

34:49.186 --> 34:51.545
burned down his cabin till
there was nothing but ashes left.

34:51.554 --> 34:55.090
Uh, newfound interest in
local history, Deputy?

34:55.126 --> 34:57.407
What if I told you I was
standing in that cabin yesterday?

34:57.428 --> 35:00.296
Well, I'd say that there
are lots of old, deserted,

35:00.331 --> 35:02.364
uh, hunting cabins in these woods.

35:02.400 --> 35:05.200
Look...

35:05.236 --> 35:07.269
I can see you believe this, Garrett,

35:07.305 --> 35:10.205
and I want to believe you,
but, I mean, you're basing this on...

35:10.241 --> 35:12.201
on some journal from over a century ago?

35:12.209 --> 35:14.176
A story like that
would've been in the papers.

35:14.211 --> 35:15.511
People would've known.

35:15.546 --> 35:17.546
What if someone didn't
want people to know?

35:21.485 --> 35:22.518
Hey.

35:22.553 --> 35:24.286
Hey.

35:26.257 --> 35:28.190
Projector's all packed up.

35:28.225 --> 35:29.325
Thanks.

35:29.360 --> 35:31.293
You're welcome.

35:31.329 --> 35:33.262
What's with the box?

35:33.297 --> 35:37.099
It's a reminder.

35:37.134 --> 35:39.168
Of...

35:39.203 --> 35:42.137
It's a reminder that no matter what,

35:42.173 --> 35:44.440
you should never
stop chasing your dreams.

35:44.475 --> 35:45.515
My life took a wrong turn.

35:45.543 --> 35:48.377
I didn't become the
person that I wanted to be.

35:48.412 --> 35:51.313
This, uh, reminds me of
when things were different.

35:56.387 --> 35:58.354
♪ ♪

36:02.259 --> 36:03.325
What's that?

36:03.394 --> 36:06.128
It's an old piece of junk.

36:06.163 --> 36:09.164
Thank you for packing up the projector.

36:09.200 --> 36:11.033
You're welcome.

36:11.068 --> 36:12.501
Mm-hmm.

36:12.536 --> 36:14.436
I'll see you later.

36:14.472 --> 36:16.105
Yes.

36:18.442 --> 36:20.376
♪ ♪

36:44.502 --> 36:46.468
What does a cult from 1871

36:46.504 --> 36:48.137
have anything to do with that lake?

36:48.172 --> 36:50.372
You didn't finish reading.

36:52.109 --> 36:54.309
Uh... "Amid many disturbing sights

36:54.345 --> 36:58.247
we found along the lake, one
in particular has haunted me..."

37:00.451 --> 37:02.284
"...a deer carcass."

37:04.188 --> 37:06.288
"Its heart was torn out in a ritual

37:06.323 --> 37:09.158
that could only be called evil."

37:09.193 --> 37:11.153
That's the thing about history, Sheriff.

37:12.530 --> 37:15.030
It repeats itself.

37:18.068 --> 37:20.402
♪ ♪

37:30.481 --> 37:33.315
[Jane's Addiction's "Jane Says" plays]

37:41.292 --> 37:44.193
♪ Jane says ♪

37:44.228 --> 37:48.063
♪ I'm done with Sergio ♪

37:48.098 --> 37:50.532
Amy: Ah, you didn't call it.

37:50.568 --> 37:52.501
[Laughter]

37:52.536 --> 37:57.372
♪ She hides the television ♪

37:57.408 --> 37:58.474
Oh, nice.

37:58.509 --> 38:00.275
Amy: Oh, we're playing.

38:00.311 --> 38:01.410
♪ Says I don't owe him nothin' ♪

38:01.445 --> 38:04.279
Yes! That was amazing!

38:04.315 --> 38:05.380
Oh! Good try, man.

38:05.416 --> 38:07.282
Good try.

38:07.318 --> 38:10.352
♪ Tell him to wait right here for me ♪

38:10.387 --> 38:15.123
♪ Or just try again tomorrow ♪

38:17.261 --> 38:21.096
♪ I'm gonna kick tomorrow ♪

38:21.131 --> 38:22.197
All right, serve it up.

38:22.233 --> 38:25.133
[Ominous music plays]

38:37.348 --> 38:40.415
Damon: We found her. Now take her.

38:40.451 --> 38:44.186
Her blood will bring yours.

38:49.326 --> 38:51.059
[Grunts]

38:53.097 --> 38:54.137
Sorry.

38:54.164 --> 38:55.197
I got it.

38:55.232 --> 38:57.132
[Indistinct conversations]

39:08.412 --> 39:11.380
Amy!

39:11.415 --> 39:14.349
Amy, come on!

39:29.233 --> 39:31.066
[Thunder rumbling]

39:33.270 --> 39:36.204
[Wind gusting]

39:36.240 --> 39:38.073
[Thunder crashes]

39:38.108 --> 39:40.108
- It's a lightning storm!
- Everybody, inside!

39:40.144 --> 39:43.045
Hey, lightning storm! Come
on, come on, come on! Hurry up!

39:43.080 --> 39:44.112
Get inside!

39:44.148 --> 39:46.114
[Indistinct shouting]

39:49.253 --> 39:51.153
Come on, guys!

39:55.125 --> 39:56.473
Amy!

40:01.165 --> 40:02.531
[Thunder crashes]

40:07.271 --> 40:09.171
Amy!

40:16.246 --> 40:18.280
It appears we were wrong.

40:18.315 --> 40:20.148
It's her.

